reviewText: La Guzmn en Primera Fila Of all the latin performers out there, Alejandra Guzman is DEFINITELY THE LATIN QUEEN OF ROCK AND ROLL ! She has diversified her repertoire over the years to include some songs in english. One of them is called "Along The Watchtower". She is a total powerhouse throughout the entire show. Easy to see why her career has lasted so long.

Great concert. I'm not her fan number 1 or 2, but since the first time that I heard the song Yo Te Esperaba I started to paid more attention to all her songs, and she really have a lot of great songs... she is a great singer and a warrior of life. Now I love a lot of her songs. I can recommend this concert to all her fans and all the people that want to watch her concerts. She have a great voice.

I had many doubts about buying this concert and after watching the doubts vanished completely.  Many of the new songs I had never heard but are instantly catchy.  The sound is just incredible and make this concert experience well worth your time.

Finally a Blu ray of this great Mexican singer !
The quality is great ! The sound is better ! The concept is an intimate concert. The song selection was great. The new songs are good ! Could be a greats hits ,if the label decided to make it a singles to the radio.

The music: the new song,
Como Ladrones.- the best song of La Guzman in many years..
Quitatelo.-  a  Catchy song,but, Beatriz Luengo has a nice voice.but, who is she ?a complete stranger in Latinamerica.
Yo no soy the nadie.- eehh, ummh, a colombian rhythm , no my favorite. Fonseca, not a fan.
